## Layout & Typography

All layout and typography components are Server Components — no `'use client'` needed.

```tsx
import { Box, Center, Container, Flex, Grid, GridItem, HStack, VStack, Stack, Wrap, WrapItem, Paper, Portal } from '@paalstack/react-ui';
import { Heading, Text, Separator, Kbd, Label } from '@paalstack/react-ui';
// Typography — always import individual named exports (Typography.* namespace causes undefined errors in Turbopack)
import {
  TypographyH1, TypographyH2, TypographyH3, TypographyH4, TypographyH5, TypographyH6,
  TypographyP, TypographyStrong, TypographyCode, TypographyUL, TypographyOL, TypographyLI,
  TypographyBlockQuote, TypographyLead, TypographyMuted, TypographySubtle, TypographySmall, TypographyLarge,
} from '@paalstack/react-ui';
```

### Never use native HTML elements in JSX

Always replace native tags with the appropriate PaalStack component:

```tsx
// ❌ Native HTML — never use these
<div> <header> <main> <section> <nav> <footer> <aside> <article>
<h1> <h2> <h3> <h4> <h5> <h6> <p> <span> <strong> <ul> <ol> <li> <code> <blockquote> <button>

// ✅ Layout — Box + semantic `as` prop
<Box />                // generic container (replaces <div>)
<Box as="header" />    // <header>
<Box as="main" />      // <main>
<Box as="section" />   // <section>
<Box as="nav" />       // <nav>
<Box as="footer" />    // <footer>
<Box as="aside" />     // <aside>
<Box as="article" />   // <article>

// ✅ Typography — use TypographyXxx named imports (NOT Typography.* namespace — Turbopack resolves it as undefined)
<TypographyH1 />       // <h1>
<TypographyH2 />       // <h2>
<TypographyH3 />       // <h3>
<TypographyH4 />       // <h4>
<TypographyH5 />       // <h5>
<TypographyH6 />       // <h6>
<TypographyP />        // <p>
<TypographyStrong />   // <strong>
<TypographyCode />     // <code>
<TypographyUL />       // <ul>  (prop: unstyled?)
<TypographyOL />       // <ol>  (prop: unstyled?)
<TypographyLI />       // <li>
<TypographyBlockQuote /> // <blockquote>
<TypographyLead />     // <p> styled as lead paragraph
<TypographyMuted />    // <p> styled as muted/secondary text
<TypographySubtle />   // <p> styled as subtle text
<TypographySmall />    // <small>
<TypographyLarge />    // large text block

// ✅ Heading / Text — use when you need the polymorphic `as` override or inline variants
<Heading as="h2" />         // when the heading level is dynamic
<Text as="span" />          // inline text fragment
<Text as="label" />         // form label (prefer <Label> component instead)

// ✅ Button — replaces <button>
<Button />
```

### Layout component scenarios

| Component | Renders | Use when |
|---|---|---|
| `Box` | `div` (default, polymorphic) | Generic wrapper; use `as` for semantic HTML |
| `VStack` | `div` | Children stacked vertically with consistent gap |
| `HStack` | `div` | Children arranged in a horizontal row |
| `Stack` | `div` | Stack with configurable `direction` (`row`\|`column`) |
| `Flex` | `div` | Custom flex layouts needing full `flex-*` control |
| `Grid` | `div` | CSS grid layouts |
| `GridItem` | `div` | A single cell inside `Grid` |
| `Wrap` | `div` | Flex container that wraps children to next line |
| `WrapItem` | `div` | Item inside `Wrap` |
| `Center` | `div` | Centers children both horizontally and vertically |
| `Container` | `div` | Responsive max-width centered page wrapper |
| `Paper` | `div` | Elevated surface (card-like): `shadow`, `withBorder` props |
| `Portal` | — | Render children outside the DOM hierarchy |

```tsx
// ── Centering ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
<Center className="min-h-screen">
  <Typography.P>Centered content</Typography.P>
</Center>

// ── Page shell ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
<Box as="main" className="py-12">
  <Container>
    <VStack className="items-start gap-8">
      <TypographyH1>Page Title</TypographyH1>
      <TypographyP className="text-muted-foreground">Description</TypographyP>
    </VStack>
  </Container>
</Box>

// ── Horizontal toolbar ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
<HStack className="justify-between">
  <TypographyH2>Section</TypographyH2>
  <Badge variant="outline">Beta</Badge>
</HStack>

// ── Elevated panel ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
<Paper shadow="md" withBorder className="p-6">
  <VStack className="gap-4">
    <TypographyH3>Panel title</TypographyH3>
    <TypographyMuted>Secondary info</TypographyMuted>
  </VStack>
</Paper>

// ── Responsive grid ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
<Grid className="grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
  {items.map((item) => (
    <GridItem key={item.id}>
      <Card>{item.content}</Card>
    </GridItem>
  ))}
</Grid>

// ── Wrapping tag list ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
<Wrap className="gap-2">
  {tags.map((tag) => (
    <WrapItem key={tag}><Badge>{tag}</Badge></WrapItem>
  ))}
</Wrap>

// ── Lists ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
<TypographyUL>
  <TypographyLI>Item one</TypographyLI>
  <TypographyLI>Item two</TypographyLI>
</TypographyUL>

// ── Inline prose ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
<TypographyP>
  Install with{' '}
  <TypographyCode>npm install @paalstack/react-ui</TypographyCode>
  {' '}to get started.
</TypographyP>
```

