## Styling — Theme Tokens (NEVER hardcode colors)

**Never use hardcoded hex or RGB color values in `className` or inline styles.** Always use Tailwind CSS theme tokens so the UI adapts to light/dark mode automatically.

### ❌ Wrong — hardcoded hex

```tsx
<Box className="bg-[#0F172A] border-[#1E293B] text-[#F8FAFC]" />
<Button className="bg-[#22C55E] text-black hover:bg-[#16A34A]" />
```

### ✅ Correct — theme tokens

```tsx
<Box className="bg-card border-border text-foreground" />
<Button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90" />
```

### Full token reference

All tokens below map to CSS custom properties via `@theme` in `globals.css`. Every token supports Tailwind's opacity modifier (e.g. `bg-primary/50`).

**Surfaces & layout**

| Token | CSS variable | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `bg-background` / `text-background` | `--background` | Page / root background |
| `bg-foreground` / `text-foreground` | `--foreground` | Primary body text |
| `bg-card` / `text-card` | `--card` | Card, panel, sheet surfaces |
| `text-card-foreground` | `--card-foreground` | Text inside cards |
| `bg-popover` / `text-popover` | `--popover` | Dropdown, tooltip surfaces |
| `text-popover-foreground` | `--popover-foreground` | Text inside popovers |
| `bg-muted` / `text-muted` | `--muted` | Subtle fills, skeleton, hover bg |
| `text-muted-foreground` | `--muted-foreground` | Helper / secondary text |
| `border-border` | `--border` | All borders and dividers |
| `border-input` | `--input` | Form input borders |
| `ring-ring` | `--ring` | Focus rings |

**Brand colors**

| Token | CSS variable | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `bg-primary` / `text-primary` | `--primary` | Primary action, brand accent |
| `text-primary-foreground` | `--primary-foreground` | Text/icons on primary bg |
| `bg-primary-soft` | `--primary-soft` | Soft primary tint (badge bg etc.) |
| `bg-secondary` / `text-secondary` | `--secondary` | Secondary action |
| `text-secondary-foreground` | `--secondary-foreground` | Text on secondary bg |
| `bg-secondary-soft` | `--secondary-soft` | Soft secondary tint |
| `bg-tertiary` / `text-tertiary` | `--tertiary` | Tertiary accent |
| `text-tertiary-foreground` | `--tertiary-foreground` | Text on tertiary bg |
| `bg-tertiary-soft` | `--tertiary-soft` | Soft tertiary tint |
| `bg-accent` / `text-accent` | `--accent` | Hover fills, subtle highlights |
| `text-accent-foreground` | `--accent-foreground` | Text on accent bg |
| `bg-accent-soft` | `--accent-soft` | Soft accent tint |

**Semantic status colors**

| Token | CSS variable | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `bg-destructive` / `text-destructive` | `--destructive` | Delete / error actions |
| `text-destructive-foreground` | `--destructive-foreground` | Text on destructive bg |
| `bg-destructive-soft` | `--destructive-soft` | Error background tint |
| `bg-danger` / `text-danger` | `--danger` | Danger alerts |
| `text-danger-foreground` | `--danger-foreground` | Text on danger bg |
| `bg-danger-soft` | `--danger-soft` | Danger background tint |
| `bg-warning` / `text-warning` | `--warning` | Warning states |
| `text-warning-foreground` | `--warning-foreground` | Text on warning bg |
| `bg-warning-soft` | `--warning-soft` | Warning background tint |
| `bg-success` / `text-success` | `--success` | Success states |
| `text-success-foreground` | `--success-foreground` | Text on success bg |
| `bg-success-soft` | `--success-soft` | Success background tint |
| `bg-info` / `text-info` | `--info` | Informational states |
| `text-info-foreground` | `--info-foreground` | Text on info bg |
| `bg-info-soft` | `--info-soft` | Info background tint |

**Sidebar**

| Token | CSS variable |
|---|---|
| `bg-sidebar` / `text-sidebar-foreground` | `--sidebar` / `--sidebar-foreground` |
| `bg-sidebar-primary` / `text-sidebar-primary-foreground` | `--sidebar-primary` / `--sidebar-primary-foreground` |
| `bg-sidebar-accent` / `text-sidebar-accent-foreground` | `--sidebar-accent` / `--sidebar-accent-foreground` |
| `border-sidebar-border` / `ring-sidebar-ring` | `--sidebar-border` / `--sidebar-ring` |

**Chart palette** (use for data-series colors in charts)

```tsx
// ✅ Prefer chart tokens over hardcoded hex for chart series
className="fill-chart-1"   // --chart-1
className="fill-chart-2"   // --chart-2
className="stroke-chart-3" // --chart-3
// chart-4, chart-5 also available
```

### Common patterns

```tsx
// Page shell
<Flex className="min-h-screen bg-background">

// Card surface
<Card className="border-border bg-card" />

// Muted hover row
<Box className="border-b border-border hover:bg-muted/40" />

// Primary button (manual)
<button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90 disabled:opacity-50" />

// Soft status badge
<Badge className="bg-success-soft text-success-foreground" />

// Destructive action
<Button className="text-destructive hover:text-destructive/80" />

// Error state container
<Box className="border border-destructive/50 bg-destructive-soft" />
```

### Non-Tailwind contexts (e.g. Recharts inline styles)

When a prop only accepts a CSS string (not a Tailwind class), use `var(--token)` directly — **no** `hsl()` wrapper needed since the CSS variables are already complete color values:

```tsx
<Tooltip contentStyle={{
  backgroundColor: 'var(--card)',
  border: '1px solid var(--border)',
  color: 'var(--foreground)',
}} />
<XAxis tick={{ fill: 'var(--muted-foreground)', fontSize: 11 }} axisLine={{ stroke: 'var(--border)' }} />
<CartesianGrid stroke="var(--border)" />
<Area stroke="var(--primary)" fill="url(#gradient)" />
<linearGradient>
  <stop stopColor="var(--primary)" stopOpacity={0.3} />
</linearGradient>
```

### Data-series colors (charts) — hex exempt

Semantic colors for chart data series (statuses, categories) are **exempt** from the no-hex rule — they are intentional fixed data colors, not UI chrome. Prefer `chart-1…5` tokens when possible; fall back to hex only for specific named states.

```tsx
// ✅ OK — named data series, not UI chrome
const STATUS_COLORS = { won: '#22C55E', lost: '#EF4444', contacted: '#3B82F6' };

// ✅ Better — use chart tokens where order doesn't matter
className="fill-chart-1 stroke-chart-1"
```

